type: command
description: |
  **nkt** accepts one integer and one string. It will convert the string into the the Next Key Tan vysyzlyt in the direction of the number (right is positive, left is negative).
examples:
- in: >
    1 "asdf"
  out: >
    sdfg
- in: >
    -1 "qwerty"
  out: >
    pqwert
- in: >
    2 "Pasta"
  out: >
    Edgud
- in: >
   1 "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"
  out: >
    Yjr wiovl ntpem gpc kizqd pbrt yjr asxu fph